{"id":80385,"title":"[Scabies: A world plague].","abstract":"Scabies is a ubiquitous contagious disease, and its prevalence is growing. Diagnostic difficulties vary according to the patient's age and health. Benzyl benzoate and ivermectin are the reference drugs in France. Decontamination of the patients' bedding, clothing, and environment is essential for successful treatment. ","date":"2014-04-16","categories":"Parasitic Diseases","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24682642","annotations":[{"name":"Disease","weight":0.781843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Health","weight":0.781524,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health"},{"name":"France","weight":0.712948,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France"},{"name":"Prevalence","weight":0.574584,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prevalence"},{"name":"Drug","weight":0.568721,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug"},{"name":"Contagious disease","weight":0.475167,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contagious_disease"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.433051,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.353863,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Bubonic plague","weight":0.297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bubonic_plague"},{"name":"Scabies","weight":0.292874,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scabies"},{"name":"Natural environment","weight":0.218291,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_environment"},{"name":"Ivermectin","weight":0.211412,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ivermectin"},{"name":"Human decontamination","weight":0.142977,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_decontamination"},{"name":"Clothing","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clothing"},{"name":"Garden","weight":0.0168623,"wik